UML:TaggedValue.value: CEDA_Model An overview diagram showing CEDA_Model Key elements and their associations.
-- Definition -- Information on publication making use of this dataset.
-- Definition -- A MO_Observation with additional attributes to cover CEDA requirements.
-- Definition -- Citation of this observation record.

-- Definition -- Brief description of the lineage of the observation. Lineage includes the background information, history of the sources of the data used and can include data quality statements [MEDIN Schema documentation version 2.3.2 , Element 17]. For example, GOSTA Sea Surface Temperature prepared by Met Office delivered to BADC on CD-ROM for inclusion in BADC Archive.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the observation metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.
-- Definition -- Category keywords, their type, and reference source.
Free text of known issues of the observation result.
-- Definition -- Date DOI assigned to observation result.
-- Definition -- Instant of resource being made available with the archive for end-user, i.e. when the resource was first issued.

UML:Constraint.name: inherited attribute inSupportOf shall be of type CEDA_Project
inherited attribute procedure shall be of type CEDA_Process
inherited attribute relatedPary shall be ordered
inherited attribute result shall be of type CEDA_Result

UML:TaggedValue.value:
-- Definition -- List of resources for and information on online observation result. Plus additional internal archiving information (e.g. curation).
-- Description -- The result can be accessed as a whole or partly.
NOTE The result may consist of segments accessible with their own resources.
-- Definition -- Curation category for backup purposes.
-- Definition -- Logical path of the result in the archive.
-- Definition -- Number of files of the result.
-- Definition -- Volume of archival holdings of result - in bytes
-- Definition -- Values of curation category for backup purposes.

CEDA_CompositeProcess a)extends MO_CompositeProcess by adding the attribute review b)restricts MO_CompositeProcess as acquisitionComponent and computationComponent are of type CEDA_Acquisition and CEDA_Processing respectively ( which requires a schematron in case of XML implementation)

For GML implementation there is the problem of multiple inheritance. However the class CEDA_Process is an abstract class without any attributes and operations therefore the solution of tagged value "gmlMixin" can be applied [ INSPIRE D2.7]
-- Definition -- A specialisation of MO_Process; an abstract class without attributes and operations. It serves as a base class for the types of processes used in CEDA model .

CEDA_CompositeProcess a)extends MO_CompositeProcess by adding the attribute review b)restricts MO_CompositeProcess as acquisitionComponent and computationComponent are of type CEDA_Acquisition and CEDA_Processing respectively ( which requires a schematron in case of XML implementation)

For GML implementation there is the problem of multiple inheritance. However the class CEDA_Process is an abstract class without any attributes and operations therefore the solution of tagged value "gmlMixin" can be applied [ INSPIRE D2.7]

-- Definition -- A MO_CompositeProcess with: a) acquisitionComponent and computationComponent of type CEDA_Acquisition and CEDA_Computation respectively. b) an additional attribute review:CEDA_Review.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the composite process metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.

UML:Constraint.name: inherited attribure computationComponent shall be of type CEDA_Processing
inherited attribute acquisitionComponent shall be of type CEDA_Acquisition

UML:TaggedValue.value: -- Definition -- A MO_Acquisition with: a) instrument, platform and operation of type CEDA_Instrument, CEDA_Platform and CEDA_Operation respectively b) an additional attribute review:CEDA_Review.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the acquisition metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.

UML:Constraint.name: inherited attribute instrument shall be of type CEDA_Instrument
inherited attribute operation shall be of type CEDA_Operation
inherited attribute plarform shall be of type CEDA_Platform

UML:TaggedValue.value: -- Definition -- A MO_Operation with details of an internal review of the metadata record.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the operation metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.

CEDA_Acquisition a)extends MO_Acquisition by adding the attribute review b)restricts MO_Acquisition as instrument, platform and operation are of type CEDA_Instrument, CEDA_Platform and CEDA_Operation respectively ( which requires a schematron in case of XML implementation)

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the instrument metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the platform metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.
-- Definition -- A MO_Processing with details of an internal review of the metadata record.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the processing metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.
CEDA_Processing only extends MO_Processing by adding the attribute review.
CEDA_Project redefines the observationCollection attribute, therefore a schematron is required for a GML implementation.
CEDA_ObservationCollection redefines the member attribute, therefore a schematron is required for a GML implementation.
CEDA_Observation redefines the inSupport attribute, therefore a schematron is required for a GML implementation.
-- Definition -- A MO_ObservationCollection with additional attributes to cover CEDA requirements.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the observation collection metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.

UML:Constraint.name: inherited attribute member shall be of type CEDA_Observation

UML:TaggedValue.value: -- Definition -- A specialisation of MO_Project which provides information on an project including relevant project services within CEDA , e.g. uploading of data.
-- Definition -- Resource relevant to the project.

-- Definition -- Details of internal metadata management of the project metadata record, i.e. creation time, last update time, record publication time ( placing metadata records into public domain), last review time.

UML:Constraint.name: inherited attribute observationCollection shall be of type CEDA_ObservationCollection

UML:TaggedValue.value: -- Definition -- Details of internal metadata records management.
-- Definition -- Internal notes pertaining to record review - including date of comments, information on the commentator and comments.
-- Definition -- Return period for standard record review.
-- Definition -- Internal notes pertaining to record metadata changes - including date of comments, information on the commentator and comments.
